The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Tryst with the peace trinity

 Three men from three different cultures, Mahatma Gandhi, Martin Luther King Jr. and Daisaku Ikeda, have followed a common path of profound dedication and achievement in improving the lives of people all over the world. Gandhi, King, Ikeda: A Legacy of Building Peace is an exhibition of vivid and inspiring images from their life stories, conveying the themes and pivotal principles in the lives of these giants of the 20th century. Hosted by Morehouse College, Atlanta, USA, Rabindra Bharati University, West Bengal Federation of UN Associations and Bharat Soka Gakkai, the show is being held with the optimism that, by examining the lives of these great figures, we may be motivated to follow their lofty ideals and philosophies in course of our daily existence. For, it is within the mundane realm of everyday life that Gandhi, King and Ikeda have sought to forge a world society and create a universal brotherhood of mankind, where all have the right to live with dignity, freedom and happiness.

 Event: An exhibition of images Gandhi, King, Ikeda: A Legacy of Building Peace

 When: Till April 20, 12 noon - 8 pm

 Where: Academy of Fine Arts; South Hall




